The original Mark ends in a sentence fragment. Apparently there is supposed
to be something else, but nobody knows (or knew) what that might be. So
early editors filled it in with various versions, one of which has come down
to us as the Orthodox version. This one happens to accord closely with the
other Three Gospels, and Acts.

Wateru's argument is that if the Ascension is missing in the Oldest Gospel,
